Senate Health and Welfare 1
Amendment No. 1 to SB1753
Crowe
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1753* House Bill No. 1770
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 63-6-204(m)(1), is amended by
adding the following as new subdivisions:
(SS) "Clinical informatics";
(TT) "Lifestyle medicine"; or
(UU) "Medical virtualist";
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 63-6-204(a)(1), is amended by
deleting the period at the end of the subdivision and substituting:
, or who determines, or causes to be determined, whether a treatment or procedure is
appropriate for the symptoms and diagnosis of such condition. This subdivision (a)(1)
does not create a private right of action.
SECTION 3. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 63-9-106(a), is amended by adding
the following immediately after the period at the end of the subsection:
The practice of osteopathic medicine also includes determining, or causing to be
determined, whether a treatment or procedure is appropriate for the symptoms and
diagnosis of another person's medical condition. This subsection does not create a
private right of action.
SECTION 4. This act takes effect upon becoming law, the public welfare requiring it,
and applies to actions occurring on or after the effective date of this act.
